---
title: Hearty Toulouse Cassoulet with a kick of Chilli
description: Much as the Italians will often add an unchopped clove of garlic to the pan to infuse just a hint of flavour, here you’ll stab the chilli and pop it in whole to release a little heat but keep things subtle. The beauty of this recipe  is that you can adjust the spice level by sticking your knife in as many times as you like. Patrick likes his cassoulet a bit cheeky so his chilli looked like a pin cushion!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/hearty-toulouse-cassoulet-3ddecb56-38a9758c.jpg
